'''Alexander Schlager''' (born 1 February 1996) is an Austrian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] club [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=A. SCHLAGER|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/alexander-schlager/245446/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=27 July 2015}}</ref>

==Club career==
Schlager started his career at [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]], before joining [[LASK]] in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportreport.biz/2017/05/29/trio-fuer-die-oberoesterreicher-aufsteiger-lask-verpflichtet-trauner-goiginger-und-schlager/ |title=Trio für die Oberösterreicher – Aufsteiger LASK verpflichtet Trauner, Goiginger und Schlager |publisher=Sportreport |language=de |date=29 May 2017 }}</ref> In May 2023, he returned to Red Bull Salzburg by signing a contract until 2027.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/aktuelles/news/alexander-schlager-kehrt-nach-salzburg-zuruck |title=Alexander Schlager kehrt nach Salzburg zurück |publisher=Red Bull Salzburg |language=de |date=30 May 2023 }}</ref>

==International career==
Schlager was the captain for [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria U-21]] in [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019 Euro U-21]].<ref>{{cite web |title=U-21 Denmark Squad|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/history/teams/200008--austria/|publisher=UEFA |access-date=5 June 2019 |date=5 June 2019 }}</ref>

On 16 November 2019, he played his first match for [[Austria national football team|Austria's national team]] in the deciding [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying|Euro 2020 qualifier]] against [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]], which ended in a 2–1 victory in Vienna.<ref>{{cite web |title=EURO 2020: MIA SAN DABEI! |url=https://www.oefb.at/News/Spielbericht-AUTMKD |website=oefb.at |publisher=[[Austrian Football Association]] |accessdate=17 November 2019 |language=de |date=16 November 2019 |archive-date=17 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117011149/https://www.oefb.at/News/Spielbericht-AUTMKD |url-status=dead }}</ref> In May 2021, he was named in the 26-man squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/Franco-Foda-fixiert-26-Spieler-umfassenden-EURO-Kader |title=Franco Foda fixiert 26 Spieler umfassenden EURO-Kader |trans-title=Franco Foda fixes the 26-player Euro squad |work=[[Austrian Football Association]] |date=24 May 2021 |access-date=24 May 2021 |language=de}}</ref> In May 2024, he sustained a knee injury which would force him to miss the upcoming [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/aktuelles/news/alex-schlager-knie-operation-06052024 |title=Update zur Verletzung von Alexander Schlager |publisher=Red Bull Salzburg |language=de |date=6 May 2024 }}</ref>

